			<CASNumber>7440-50-8</CASNumber>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Copper scrap refers to the recovery and processing of copper materials from end-of-life products and structures such as cars, buildings, and electrical appliances. It is separated from other materials and sent to scrap metal recycling centers, where it undergoes urban mining. This process involves melting down the copper and casting it into new products. In the U.S., approximately 830,000 tonnes of copper scrap were recycled in 2022, accounting for 32% of the total U.S. copper supply for that year.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">废铜是指从报废产品和结构（如汽车、建筑物和电器）中回收和加工铜材料。它与其他材料分离并送往废金属回收中心，在那里进行城市采矿。这个过程包括熔化铜并将其铸造成新产品。在美国，2022 年回收了约 830,000 吨废铜，占当年美国铜供应总量的 32%。</common:generalComment>
